Description: Mosaic glass inlay: moulded red-glass square inlaid with a mosaic glass wedjat-eye facing left. The eye is opaque white with yellow eyebrow on a black field. The falcon markings under the eye are in opaque white, turquoise-blue, black, and yellow. Assembled from three pieces. The eye was set into a square opening in the centre of the inlay and was filled in and held in place with resin. From a naos.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Temple of Hathor (Dendara), Temple of Hathor
Bibliographic references: Tait 1991 / Five Thousand Years of Glass (pl.61)
